external_knowledge:
- "electoral landscape" refers to the distribution of votes among candidates across different precincts;
- "strongholds" refers to the precincts where candidates have received a significant number of votes;
- "bastions of support" refers to the precincts where candidates have a strong presence or have received a substantial number of votes.

sql:
SELECT v.vote_id, c.candidate_id, c.name, p.precinct_id, v.votes
FROM votes v
JOIN candidates c ON v.candidate_id = c.candidate_id
JOIN precincts p ON v.precinct_id = p.precinct_id
WHERE c.office_id IN (
    SELECT office_id FROM offices WHERE election_id = (
        SELECT election_id FROM elections WHERE election_type = 'General' AND election_year = 2020
    )
);
